<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>KOS List and Rule IV</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:14 p.m. 19/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> KOS List and Rule IV<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1550" TARGET=_self>Re: PvP KOS list?</A> (Stupid)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Plug of The Pluggers started a lamers/KOS list. They always make one, and there are a few names on it already. It will probably get incorporated into an IRC server bot, but for now you can read www.thepluggers.org and you should find a list growing there. It would be nice if a site could sponsor one.
<P>IV. Thou shalt not loot fallen members of thine own race except to save their item and coins for them (unless perhaps no one is looking...).
<P>&gt; Where can one find this list? I'm not a Halfling, but I think
<BR>&gt; that for a working PvP community to form we need to be able to
<BR>&gt; weed out the "bad apples" as quickly as possible. A
<BR>&gt; server-wide ooc community will help breed individual
<BR>&gt; in-character communities.
<P>&gt; In my opinion, the "Three Commandements" on Rellos Zek
<BR>&gt; are:
<P>&gt; I: Thou Shalt Not Kill Thine OWN Race
<P>&gt; This is a Role Playing game. If you want to kill, do it "in
<BR>&gt; character". There is a city full of victims only a few
<BR>&gt; zones away. If you want to go on a mindless killing spree, do it
<BR>&gt; there.
<BR>&gt; (In time, faction hits will enforce this rule for us.)
<P>&gt; II: Thou Shalt Not Kill Newbies of ANY Race
<P>&gt; Creating a Monk and going to Erudin where the weakling mages can
<BR>&gt; be pummeled to death by the hordes is not good for anyone. You
<BR>&gt; want to fight, fine. It is a PvP server. We all acknowledge
<BR>&gt; that. But pick a fight that is at least -reasonably- fair.
<BR>&gt; That's why it's called a "PvP server" and not a
<BR>&gt; "PK server". PvP implies that both sides fight; PK
<BR>&gt; does not.
<P>&gt; III: Thou Shalt Not CAMP on Corpses
<P>&gt; You already killed them once, when they were fully equipped and
<BR>&gt; able to defend themselves. What makes you think that the fight
<BR>&gt; will be any more "fair" when they come crawling back
<BR>&gt; with no armor, no weapon and few (if any) spells readied? Take
<BR>&gt; your one item as loot and move on. (If it helps, imagine that
<BR>&gt; they are coming back with two or three VERY powerful friends
<BR>&gt; that will kick you so hard that you'll wish you never saw them
<BR>&gt; in the first place.)
<P>&gt; Additions welcome.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
